      "message": "this would make it perform a disk write on happy path, which could be quite noticeable for slower or heavy-loaded HDDs. Another thing is that |Empty| was a placeholder for an enum value 0 which is kind of required for protobufs, but not really supposed to be used. I\u0027m not sure if all other parts of the code handle it correctly\n\nCould you please change the saveFailure() function to (1) not write the protobuf if it already has the same failure reason as we\u0027re trying to save, and (2) change |Empty| failure to not having it set at all",
      "range": {
